article.headline: White pours in 28 points
article.linkText: Mississippi State upends No. 20 Louisiana Tech
article.story:
STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) -- A typical night for Tan White at
Mississippi State led to a rare upset of Louisiana Tech.

White scored 28 points to lead the Bulldogs to a 72-55 upset of
the Lady Techsters (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today; No. 21 AP) on Tuesday night.

White scored at least 20 points for the fourth time this season
for Mississippi State (3-2), which made 43 percent (26-of-60) of
their shots and beat the Lady Techsters for the first time since
1999.

"You can see this team starting to grow and communicate
better," Mississippi State coach Sharon Fanning said. "Our
defense was great. This is as good of a win as I have experienced.
I can't think of any aspects of this game that were not positive."

Tiania Burns had 13 points despite a sore shoulder and Blessing
Chekwa added 10 for Mississippi State, which has won two straight.

"You don't feel the pain when you're out there," Burns said.

Shan Moore led Louisiana Tech (2-1) with 17 points, and Tasha
Crain added 16. Leading scorer Lakiste Barkus, who entered
averaging 17.5 points, was held to three points on 1-of-12
shooting.

"We have a lot of players playing that have never been the
go-to player," Louisiana Tech coach Kurt Badke said. "They are
having to adjust. It's like taking Tan White out of the lineup.
It's going to shake some things up."

Louisiana Tech shot just 32 percent (9-for-28) in the first
half, and trailed 32-20 at halftime.

The Bulldogs, who lost 66-49 to No. 9 Baylor at home last week,
improved to 52-5 in non-conference home games under coach Fanning.

"We expect to win big games like this this year," Fanning
said.
